<paragraph blockId="3.[151,588,331,390]" box="[151,288,366,390]" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">
(
<figureCitation box="[159,280,366,390]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 12" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1824,1847]" captionTargetBox="[234,1369,199,1747]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[205,1381,193,1788]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 12. Lepidostoma species. Figs. 1 – 6, Lepidostoma kashmiricum sp. nov.: 1, 3 genitalia, dorsal view; 2, 3 genitalia, ventral view; 3, 3 genitalia, left lateral view; 4, phallic apparatus, left lateral view. 5, right forewing, dorsal view; 6, head, scape, and palps, right lateral view. Figs. 7 – 12, Lepidostoma himachalicum sp. nov.: 7, 3 genitalia, dorsal view; 8, 3 genitalia ventral view; 9, 3 genitalia, left lateral view; 10, phallic apparatus, left lateral view; 11, right forewing, dorsal view; 12, head, scape and palps, right lateral view. BPIA = basal process of inferior appendage; dc = discoidal cell; F 1 = fork 1; F 2 = fork 2; IF = inferior appendage; LP = labial palp; IX = segment IX; MP = maxillary palp; P = phallus; PS = parameres; PCF = postcubital fold; S = scape; X = segment X." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/206993/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">
Figs. 
<number box="[223,280,366,390]" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" value="9.5" valueMax="12.0" valueMin="7.0">7–12</number>
</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,438,894]" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">
Male: Golden brown. Scapes (
<figureCitation box="[501,585,438,462]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 12" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1824,1847]" captionTargetBox="[234,1369,199,1747]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[205,1381,193,1788]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 12. Lepidostoma species. Figs. 1 – 6, Lepidostoma kashmiricum sp. nov.: 1, 3 genitalia, dorsal view; 2, 3 genitalia, ventral view; 3, 3 genitalia, left lateral view; 4, phallic apparatus, left lateral view. 5, right forewing, dorsal view; 6, head, scape, and palps, right lateral view. Figs. 7 – 12, Lepidostoma himachalicum sp. nov.: 7, 3 genitalia, dorsal view; 8, 3 genitalia ventral view; 9, 3 genitalia, left lateral view; 10, phallic apparatus, left lateral view; 11, right forewing, dorsal view; 12, head, scape and palps, right lateral view. BPIA = basal process of inferior appendage; dc = discoidal cell; F 1 = fork 1; F 2 = fork 2; IF = inferior appendage; LP = labial palp; IX = segment IX; MP = maxillary palp; P = phallus; PS = parameres; PCF = postcubital fold; S = scape; X = segment X." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/206993/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">
Fig. 
<number box="[556,585,438,462]" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" value="12.0">12</number>
</figureCitation>
) each 2.88 mm., with 
<number box="[848,862,438,462]" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" value="2.0">2</number>
posterior processes, basal process slightly shorter than apical process, apex membranous. Maxillary palps (
<figureCitation box="[792,866,474,498]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 12" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1824,1847]" captionTargetBox="[234,1369,199,1747]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[205,1381,193,1788]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 12. Lepidostoma species. Figs. 1 – 6, Lepidostoma kashmiricum sp. nov.: 1, 3 genitalia, dorsal view; 2, 3 genitalia, ventral view; 3, 3 genitalia, left lateral view; 4, phallic apparatus, left lateral view. 5, right forewing, dorsal view; 6, head, scape, and palps, right lateral view. Figs. 7 – 12, Lepidostoma himachalicum sp. nov.: 7, 3 genitalia, dorsal view; 8, 3 genitalia ventral view; 9, 3 genitalia, left lateral view; 10, phallic apparatus, left lateral view; 11, right forewing, dorsal view; 12, head, scape and palps, right lateral view. BPIA = basal process of inferior appendage; dc = discoidal cell; F 1 = fork 1; F 2 = fork 2; IF = inferior appendage; LP = labial palp; IX = segment IX; MP = maxillary palp; P = phallus; PS = parameres; PCF = postcubital fold; S = scape; X = segment X." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/206993/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">
Fig. 
<number box="[838,866,474,498]" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" value="12.0">12</number>
</figureCitation>
) long, each 0.96 mm, 
<number box="[1120,1133,474,498]" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" value="2.0">2</number>
-segmented, basal segment 
<number box="[151,165,510,534]" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" value="3.0">3</number>
times longer than terminal segment. Length of each forewing 
<quantity box="[864,946,510,534]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" unit="mm" value="10.0">10 mm</quantity>
. Wing venation and setae as in 
<figureCitation box="[1297,1379,510,534]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 12" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1824,1847]" captionTargetBox="[234,1369,199,1747]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[205,1381,193,1788]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 12. Lepidostoma species. Figs. 1 – 6, Lepidostoma kashmiricum sp. nov.: 1, 3 genitalia, dorsal view; 2, 3 genitalia, ventral view; 3, 3 genitalia, left lateral view; 4, phallic apparatus, left lateral view. 5, right forewing, dorsal view; 6, head, scape, and palps, right lateral view. Figs. 7 – 12, Lepidostoma himachalicum sp. nov.: 7, 3 genitalia, dorsal view; 8, 3 genitalia ventral view; 9, 3 genitalia, left lateral view; 10, phallic apparatus, left lateral view; 11, right forewing, dorsal view; 12, head, scape and palps, right lateral view. BPIA = basal process of inferior appendage; dc = discoidal cell; F 1 = fork 1; F 2 = fork 2; IF = inferior appendage; LP = labial palp; IX = segment IX; MP = maxillary palp; P = phallus; PS = parameres; PCF = postcubital fold; S = scape; X = segment X." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/206993/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">
Fig. 
<number box="[1349,1379,510,534]" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" value="11.0">11</number>
</figureCitation>
. Male Genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[337,463,546,570]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 12" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1824,1847]" captionTargetBox="[234,1369,199,1747]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[205,1381,193,1788]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 12. Lepidostoma species. Figs. 1 – 6, Lepidostoma kashmiricum sp. nov.: 1, 3 genitalia, dorsal view; 2, 3 genitalia, ventral view; 3, 3 genitalia, left lateral view; 4, phallic apparatus, left lateral view. 5, right forewing, dorsal view; 6, head, scape, and palps, right lateral view. Figs. 7 – 12, Lepidostoma himachalicum sp. nov.: 7, 3 genitalia, dorsal view; 8, 3 genitalia ventral view; 9, 3 genitalia, left lateral view; 10, phallic apparatus, left lateral view; 11, right forewing, dorsal view; 12, head, scape and palps, right lateral view. BPIA = basal process of inferior appendage; dc = discoidal cell; F 1 = fork 1; F 2 = fork 2; IF = inferior appendage; LP = labial palp; IX = segment IX; MP = maxillary palp; P = phallus; PS = parameres; PCF = postcubital fold; S = scape; X = segment X." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/206993/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">
Figs. 
<number box="[402,463,546,570]" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" value="8.5" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="7.0">7–10</number>
</figureCitation>
): Apical margin of segment IX pentagonal in dorsal view. Tergum X forming pair of spanner-shaped plates, each deeply notched apicolaterally. Inferior appendages each 
<number box="[1095,1110,582,606]" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" value="2.0">2</number>
- segmented, first article long and broad, second article shorter and shallowly excised at its apex. Phallus slender; phallobase truncate apically; parameres set across genitalia; phallicata slender, slanting downward.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="28" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,438,894]" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,319,690,715]" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species differs from other species of the 
<taxonomicName authority="Branch" authorityName="Branch" box="[854,1032,690,715]" class="Insecta" family="Lepidostomatidae" genus="Lepidostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ferox">
<emphasis box="[854,943,691,715]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">L. ferox</emphasis>
Branch
</taxonomicName>
in having the halves of segment X spanner-shaped and apicolaterally notched.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="28" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,438,894]" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,331,763,787]" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name of the species is based on the state “Himachal Pradesh” from where the 
<typeStatus box="[1274,1322,763,787]" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">type</typeStatus>
specimen was collected.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
